WEBVTT

00:00:00.590 --> 00:00:05.990
The next part is a video entitled The Inside Story hosted by

00:00:05.990 --> 00:00:11.390
Brother Ken Stovall, who also serves as a Theocratic School

00:00:11.390 --> 00:00:42.710
instructor.

00:00:42.710 --> 00:00:46.810
I am so excited to be with you here again on this segment of

00:00:46.810 --> 00:00:48.310
The Inside Story.

00:00:48.310 --> 00:00:52.310
This time we're with class number 143 of the Gilead School.

00:00:52.310 --> 00:00:56.509
And you are going to meet some adorable brothers and sisters.

00:00:56.509 --> 00:01:00.109
And let me tell you, they have some moving experiences to

00:01:00.109 --> 00:01:01.310
relate to you.

00:01:01.310 --> 00:01:05.310
And we're going to solve two fascinating mysteries.

00:01:05.310 --> 00:01:06.709
And we have music.

00:01:06.709 --> 00:01:09.510
Students in this class are going to thrill you with their

00:01:09.510 --> 00:01:10.909
musical talent.

00:01:10.909 --> 00:01:13.510
There is a captivating song that they're going to sing for

00:01:13.510 --> 00:01:14.510
you.

00:01:14.510 --> 00:01:23.260
So come with me as we together get the Inside Story.

00:01:23.260 --> 00:01:25.060
Let's introduce our first guest.

00:01:25.060 --> 00:01:37.920
And that would be Sasha Komoromi from the Serbia branch.

00:01:37.920 --> 00:01:42.519
So Brother Komoromi, you serve at the Serbia branch.

00:01:42.519 --> 00:01:46.319
But you told me that some years ago, before you were in

00:01:46.319 --> 00:01:49.719
the truth, you discovered that there were two main interests

00:01:49.719 --> 00:01:51.120
you had in life.

00:01:51.120 --> 00:01:52.920
One of them had to do with a career choice.

00:01:52.920 --> 00:01:54.120
Could you explain that?

00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:56.120
One was music.

00:01:56.120 --> 00:01:57.319
Music.

00:01:57.319 --> 00:02:02.319
Now, is this a picture of you?

00:02:02.319 --> 00:02:05.420
That was the old name.

00:02:05.420 --> 00:02:07.719
Evidently you were in a band.

00:02:07.719 --> 00:02:12.919
Yes, we were at one competition at that time.

00:02:12.919 --> 00:02:14.919
That was one of your interests.

00:02:14.919 --> 00:02:16.219
But there was another.

00:02:16.219 --> 00:02:17.120
What was that?

00:02:17.120 --> 00:02:18.919
Searching for purpose of life.

00:02:18.919 --> 00:02:21.919
And how did you go about searching for life's purpose?

00:02:21.919 --> 00:02:27.120
I read a lot of books, books about parapsychology,

00:02:27.120 --> 00:02:30.919
Buddhism, spiritism, Tibetan Lamaism.

00:02:30.919 --> 00:02:33.120
Amazing, that's a lot of books.

00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:38.020
Now, at the time, though, you were dating your wife, Vicky,

00:02:38.020 --> 00:02:40.120
what did she think of all these books?

00:02:40.120 --> 00:02:43.319
Did she share your interest in all this reading?

00:02:43.319 --> 00:02:47.419
I wish she did, but no, she did not.

00:02:47.419 --> 00:02:51.620
To be honest, it's not really easy to like, to read

00:02:51.620 --> 00:02:52.620
that kind of books.

00:02:52.620 --> 00:02:57.520
For example, the book of the dead, the book of the dead,

00:02:57.520 --> 00:03:02.120
that I can see that's not going to be a very enjoyable book.

00:03:02.120 --> 00:03:04.020
Now, was it only books?

00:03:04.020 --> 00:03:07.120
Is that the only way you were searching for the purpose of life?

00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:12.620
No, I was also experimented with different states of mind

00:03:12.620 --> 00:03:18.620
under influences of drugs during my hallucinations.

00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:21.819
I had many things already solved out.

00:03:21.819 --> 00:03:23.819
You had everything solved.

00:03:23.819 --> 00:03:25.319
This is what I thought.

00:03:25.319 --> 00:03:31.020
But after I come to myself again

00:03:31.120 --> 00:03:35.020
and I'm again in the same room and everything is the same.

00:03:35.020 --> 00:03:37.520
So I was really, really disappointed.

00:03:37.520 --> 00:03:39.719
And then I prayed to God.

00:03:39.719 --> 00:03:43.719
I said, God, I'm asking just for one thing.

00:03:43.719 --> 00:03:47.319
Whatever it is, just please help me to be certain

00:03:47.319 --> 00:03:48.919
that I find the truth.

00:03:48.919 --> 00:03:49.719
Very interesting.

00:03:49.719 --> 00:03:52.620
So you prayed for Jehovah to help you find the truth.

00:03:52.620 --> 00:03:55.719
Of course, you didn't know Jehovah at the time.

00:03:55.719 --> 00:03:58.919
So how was your prayer answered?

00:03:59.020 --> 00:04:01.620
As soon after that, I went to Germany.

00:04:01.620 --> 00:04:04.919
I had the idea to form my music studio.

00:04:04.919 --> 00:04:09.020
During my visit there, I understood that my uncle

00:04:09.020 --> 00:04:11.520
and my aunt, David Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:04:11.520 --> 00:04:12.819
And you never knew that before?

00:04:12.819 --> 00:04:14.219
No, no, I didn't know.

00:04:14.219 --> 00:04:17.220
So what did they have in their home

00:04:17.220 --> 00:04:20.620
that would have been really exciting to you?

00:04:20.620 --> 00:04:22.720
As all Jehovah's Witnesses,

00:04:22.720 --> 00:04:26.620
they had a lot of telecratic books.

00:04:26.620 --> 00:04:28.720
So did you read the books?

00:04:28.720 --> 00:04:31.120
Yes, I read them a lot.

00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:34.120
Actually, I read the book daily.

00:04:34.120 --> 00:04:34.819
Wow.

00:04:34.819 --> 00:04:38.519
So you get back home, you open up the suitcases

00:04:38.519 --> 00:04:42.519
and Vicki's there and she sees books.

00:04:42.519 --> 00:04:45.319
And you were supposed to bring home musical equipment.

00:04:45.319 --> 00:04:47.519
What did she think about that?

00:04:47.519 --> 00:04:53.699
She thought, now definitely she's totally crazy.

00:04:53.699 --> 00:04:55.899
So what did you do?

00:04:55.899 --> 00:04:59.300
I explained very immediately that from now on

00:04:59.300 --> 00:05:01.899
I would like to leave according to what they read

00:05:01.899 --> 00:05:04.000
in these books and the Bible.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:07.800
And I also would like for her that she also

00:05:07.800 --> 00:05:08.600
leave like that.

00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:11.600
If this is okay with her, we can say together

00:05:11.600 --> 00:05:16.100
if it is not okay with her, we are finished.

00:05:16.100 --> 00:05:18.199
You like to be direct, don't you?

00:05:18.199 --> 00:05:22.199
I know, I was very tactful.

00:05:22.199 --> 00:05:26.100
But I also offered her a book, Young People Ask.

00:05:26.100 --> 00:05:27.100
Did she like that?

00:05:27.199 --> 00:05:30.500
Yes, she liked that much more than my ultimate.

00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:31.500
I see.

00:05:31.500 --> 00:05:34.500
We start studying the Bible.

00:05:34.500 --> 00:05:38.100
At the beginning my wife, she started because of me.

00:05:38.100 --> 00:05:40.500
But later she done this because of her.

00:05:40.500 --> 00:05:45.199
And after six months, we became unbaptized publishers.

00:05:45.199 --> 00:05:50.699
Then we get married and we were baptized at 1994.

00:05:50.699 --> 00:05:53.600
Immediately we start with full-time service

00:05:53.600 --> 00:05:57.199
and we served five years as regular pioneers.

00:05:57.199 --> 00:06:00.600
Then almost five years as special pioneers

00:06:00.600 --> 00:06:05.300
and now we are 13 years in the Serbia branch.

00:06:05.300 --> 00:06:08.199
Jehovah has answered your prayer, you're satisfied.

00:06:08.199 --> 00:06:10.100
You found the truth.

00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:12.899
You found the purpose in life.

00:06:12.899 --> 00:06:16.000
But there's still the music.

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:19.899
Did you have to give up your desire to play music,

00:06:19.899 --> 00:06:23.100
to be involved in music, especially since you've come to Bethel now?

00:06:23.100 --> 00:06:27.000
Actually, in 2013 there was one idea

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:32.300
that we should start with project recording vocal rendition

00:06:32.300 --> 00:06:34.199
of our teocratic songs.

00:06:34.199 --> 00:06:37.899
And my wife Violeta and I had privileged to participate

00:06:37.899 --> 00:06:38.899
in that project.

00:06:38.899 --> 00:06:41.199
Now, was this just for the Serbia branch?

00:06:41.199 --> 00:06:41.899
No.

00:06:41.899 --> 00:06:42.600
No.

00:06:42.600 --> 00:06:46.899
Plan was to record the songs in four or five languages.

00:06:46.899 --> 00:06:48.800
Four or five languages.

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:50.899
Would this mean that you would travel around

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:53.500
into the different countries surrounding Serbia?

00:06:53.500 --> 00:06:54.500
No.

00:06:54.500 --> 00:06:59.500
Ideas was that singers will come from other countries to Serbia

00:06:59.500 --> 00:07:02.500
and they will be full-time singers

00:07:02.500 --> 00:07:05.399
for a period of time until we finish that project.

00:07:05.399 --> 00:07:07.899
That must have been a tremendous amount of work.

00:07:07.899 --> 00:07:10.100
How did you get that accomplished?

00:07:10.100 --> 00:07:13.000
Yeah, it's easier if we see one video

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:15.199
and it will be much more understandable.

00:07:15.199 --> 00:07:15.699
All right.

00:07:15.699 --> 00:07:16.199
Good.

00:07:16.199 --> 00:07:19.399
Let's watch the video.

00:07:19.399 --> 00:07:24.899
One of the first things we needed was a recording studio.

00:07:24.899 --> 00:07:34.259
So with the help of many, we built our own.

00:07:34.259 --> 00:07:41.069
A typical day began with a little music theory,

00:07:41.069 --> 00:07:43.069
a little stretching,

00:07:43.069 --> 00:07:49.040
and a brief review of the song's scriptural theme.

00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:51.540
Once they received a new song,

00:07:51.540 --> 00:07:55.439
they practiced in separate groups.

00:07:55.439 --> 00:08:00.519
Then they would all come together.

00:08:00.519 --> 00:08:04.720
Finally, it was time to record.

00:08:04.720 --> 00:08:09.220
This resulted in 450 songs being recorded

00:08:09.220 --> 00:08:21.649
in a period of 22 months.

00:08:30.310 --> 00:08:31.509
Looking back,

00:08:31.509 --> 00:08:34.909
these songs were sung not just with words,

00:08:34.909 --> 00:08:44.350
but with hearts full of love for Jehovah.

00:08:44.350 --> 00:08:49.750
Look at them.

00:08:49.750 --> 00:08:51.750
They were nice readings at the end.

00:08:51.750 --> 00:08:52.549
My surprise.

00:08:52.549 --> 00:08:54.149
I loved the way the chorus sounded.

00:08:54.149 --> 00:08:55.250
You did a good job with them.

00:08:55.250 --> 00:08:59.049
That must have been a tremendous amount of work.

00:08:59.049 --> 00:09:00.149
Getting that all done though,

00:09:00.149 --> 00:09:01.649
in five different languages.

00:09:01.649 --> 00:09:04.149
Yes, singers, they done a great job

00:09:04.149 --> 00:09:06.049
and also old crew.

00:09:06.049 --> 00:09:08.750
And we really could see all the times

00:09:08.750 --> 00:09:10.149
they are in love for Jehovah,

00:09:10.149 --> 00:09:11.750
love for brotherhood.

00:09:11.750 --> 00:09:13.350
And every day,

00:09:13.350 --> 00:09:16.450
we can see a lot of self-sacrificing spirit.

00:09:16.450 --> 00:09:18.250
Now, Sasha, let me ask you one more question.

00:09:18.250 --> 00:09:21.049
We saw the picture there of you as a musician.

00:09:21.049 --> 00:09:23.950
And I know you have some musical talent.

00:09:23.950 --> 00:09:26.149
Possibly you could have become famous.

00:09:26.149 --> 00:09:29.450
Do you ever regret not pursuing some sort of a career

00:09:29.450 --> 00:09:32.649
in the world as opposed to giving your life

00:09:32.649 --> 00:09:33.450
in full-time service?

00:09:33.450 --> 00:09:34.450
Did you, Jehovah?

00:09:34.450 --> 00:09:35.649
As you said,

00:09:35.649 --> 00:09:40.250
I could be famous or I could become a drug addict

00:09:40.250 --> 00:09:42.049
and now dead.

00:09:42.049 --> 00:09:43.750
That's a good voice.

00:09:43.750 --> 00:09:46.850
But no, no regrets at all.

00:09:46.850 --> 00:09:52.450
I received much, much more that I ever imagined.

00:09:52.549 --> 00:09:55.450
And in my case, from my first prayer,

00:09:55.450 --> 00:09:57.149
till now, Jehovah ensured me

00:09:57.149 --> 00:10:00.049
that he's really here of prayers,

00:10:00.049 --> 00:10:04.149
as Solomon mentioned in Psalm 65 verse two.

00:10:04.149 --> 00:10:05.850
Excellent, thank you so much, Sasha,

00:10:05.850 --> 00:10:08.850
for sharing these very heartfelt comments.

00:10:08.850 --> 00:10:17.649
And thank you.

00:10:17.649 --> 00:10:19.350
Now, you know what we're going to do?

00:10:19.350 --> 00:10:21.549
We're going to give you opportunity

00:10:21.549 --> 00:10:24.850
to get to know some of the students in our audience.

00:10:24.850 --> 00:10:27.049
We're going to do an activity I call

00:10:27.049 --> 00:10:28.850
what's my favorite scripture?

00:10:28.850 --> 00:10:30.450
So we're going to ask the students

00:10:30.450 --> 00:10:33.049
if they'll volunteer and give us their favorite scripture.

00:10:33.049 --> 00:10:34.049
And in a minute or less,

00:10:34.049 --> 00:10:38.049
tell us what it says and why it's their favorite scripture.

00:10:38.049 --> 00:10:39.350
Okay.

00:10:39.350 --> 00:10:42.860
Let's see now.

00:10:42.860 --> 00:10:45.360
Who would like to go first?

00:10:45.360 --> 00:10:49.460
Shingurai Mapfumo from Zimbabwe.

00:10:49.460 --> 00:10:51.460
Psalm 84 verse 11.

00:10:51.460 --> 00:10:53.960
And what does that say?

00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:57.659
For Jehovah God is a sun and a shield.

00:10:57.659 --> 00:10:59.960
He gives favor and glory.

00:11:00.059 --> 00:11:02.960
Jehovah will not hold back anything good

00:11:02.960 --> 00:11:04.860
from those walking in integrity.

00:11:04.860 --> 00:11:05.759
Okay, so tell us.

00:11:05.759 --> 00:11:07.659
Why is that your favorite scripture?

00:11:07.659 --> 00:11:11.360
During the economic crisis in Zimbabwe,

00:11:11.360 --> 00:11:14.159
my partner, Patna and I ran out of food.

00:11:14.159 --> 00:11:16.460
We were really starving.

00:11:16.460 --> 00:11:18.159
And physically, we were so weak

00:11:18.159 --> 00:11:20.159
that we could not even function.

00:11:20.159 --> 00:11:21.759
Still, we managed to go to town

00:11:21.759 --> 00:11:24.759
hoping that we could get some money from the bank.

00:11:24.759 --> 00:11:26.659
There was a long queue.

00:11:26.659 --> 00:11:29.460
And the bank was not giving any money either.

00:11:29.460 --> 00:11:31.559
We were so distraught.

00:11:31.559 --> 00:11:35.159
At that moment, when we didn't know what to do,

00:11:35.159 --> 00:11:37.259
a truck from the branch office

00:11:37.259 --> 00:11:40.259
brought food supplies for us,

00:11:40.259 --> 00:11:42.259
then it became so clear to me

00:11:42.259 --> 00:11:44.759
that Jehovah is a shield

00:11:44.759 --> 00:11:46.860
and he never holds back anything good

00:11:46.860 --> 00:11:48.659
from his loyal servants.

00:11:48.659 --> 00:11:49.559
Amazing.

00:11:49.559 --> 00:11:51.360
Well, I can see why that's your favorite scripture.

00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:53.059
All right, who else?

00:11:53.059 --> 00:11:54.860
Let's get sister.

00:11:54.860 --> 00:11:56.460
It's a Peng Mushongo.

00:11:56.460 --> 00:11:58.960
And she's from South Africa.

00:11:58.960 --> 00:12:02.360
My favorite scripture is Psalm 68 verse 5.

00:12:02.360 --> 00:12:04.860
And it says about Jehovah.

00:12:04.860 --> 00:12:06.759
He is the father of the fatherless

00:12:06.759 --> 00:12:08.759
and a protector of leaders.

00:12:08.759 --> 00:12:10.860
Why is that your favorite scripture?

00:12:10.860 --> 00:12:12.059
Well, I became motherless

00:12:12.059 --> 00:12:14.559
when I was only one year old.

00:12:14.559 --> 00:12:16.860
But Jehovah has provided me

00:12:16.860 --> 00:12:19.759
with hundreds of mothers around the globe,

00:12:19.759 --> 00:12:22.460
both black and white.

00:12:22.460 --> 00:12:25.059
And because a battle work

00:12:25.059 --> 00:12:28.460
involves traveling all around the African continent,

00:12:28.460 --> 00:12:30.559
working with the translators,

00:12:30.559 --> 00:12:32.860
it makes it even more precious to me

00:12:32.860 --> 00:12:36.259
that I adopt this family wherever we go.

00:12:36.259 --> 00:12:39.360
Truly, Jehovah has proved to be my father

00:12:39.360 --> 00:12:42.360
and my protector to this day.

00:12:42.360 --> 00:12:43.159
Very touching.

00:12:43.159 --> 00:12:45.360
And I'm sure that all of those parents

00:12:45.360 --> 00:12:49.460
that have adopted you are proud to have you as a daughter.

00:12:49.460 --> 00:12:51.759
Who else could tell us their favorite scripture?

00:12:51.759 --> 00:12:55.759
All right, let's get brother Sylvain Bois from Benin.

00:12:55.759 --> 00:12:59.460
It is Psalm 94 verse 18 and 19.

00:12:59.460 --> 00:13:00.960
And what does it say?

00:13:00.960 --> 00:13:02.559
Your loyal love,

00:13:02.559 --> 00:13:05.960
O Jehovah, kept supporting me.

00:13:05.960 --> 00:13:08.559
When anxieties overwhelm me,

00:13:08.559 --> 00:13:11.559
you comforted and soothed me.

00:13:11.559 --> 00:13:12.559
So tell us,

00:13:12.559 --> 00:13:15.360
why is that scripture special to you?

00:13:15.360 --> 00:13:16.360
Years ago,

00:13:16.360 --> 00:13:19.059
when I was attending Minnesota training school,

00:13:19.059 --> 00:13:20.960
I had a serious stroke

00:13:20.960 --> 00:13:23.159
and I was hospitalized.

00:13:23.159 --> 00:13:25.659
When I woke from coma,

00:13:25.860 --> 00:13:28.559
I felt very happy because I was alive

00:13:28.559 --> 00:13:30.759
but also very discouraged.

00:13:30.759 --> 00:13:33.860
Because I thought everything was over for me.

00:13:33.860 --> 00:13:36.159
Pioneer service, school,

00:13:36.159 --> 00:13:40.559
and even my dream to become one day a missionary.

00:13:40.559 --> 00:13:43.159
But one of the instructor and his wife

00:13:43.159 --> 00:13:44.759
came to the hospital

00:13:44.759 --> 00:13:46.960
and they read me that verse.

00:13:46.960 --> 00:13:50.159
And my heart was full of anxieties

00:13:50.159 --> 00:13:51.960
but that really felt that day

00:13:52.059 --> 00:13:56.360
that Jehovah was able to comfort me and soothed me.

00:13:56.360 --> 00:13:57.360
And you know what,

00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:58.860
one year later,

00:13:58.860 --> 00:14:02.159
I was permitted to attend again, MTS.

00:14:02.159 --> 00:14:03.960
And few months later,

00:14:03.960 --> 00:14:06.460
Jehovah fulfilled another of my dream

00:14:06.460 --> 00:14:09.259
as I've been assigned as a missionary in Africa.

00:14:09.259 --> 00:14:10.059
Brother Bois,

00:14:10.059 --> 00:14:11.059
that was very touching.

00:14:11.059 --> 00:14:11.960
Thank you so much.

00:14:11.960 --> 00:14:14.659
And we're so glad to have you in this class of Gileon.

00:14:14.659 --> 00:14:20.820
Well, that's all we're going to have time for.

00:14:20.820 --> 00:14:24.220
So now it's time to introduce our next guest.

00:14:24.320 --> 00:14:26.519
And that would be Brother Paulo Magaña

00:14:26.519 --> 00:14:37.620
and he's from Brazil.

00:14:37.620 --> 00:14:40.019
Now, Brother Magaña, you're at the Brazil branch

00:14:40.019 --> 00:14:43.320
but you came in the truth at nine years old

00:14:43.320 --> 00:14:45.419
at the same time as your mother.

00:14:45.419 --> 00:14:47.120
And you went to the branch,

00:14:47.120 --> 00:14:49.820
then to Bethel in your early 20s.

00:14:49.820 --> 00:14:53.019
And you've been there for 27 years.

00:14:53.019 --> 00:14:55.620
