And then you started pioneering at the age of 15.

00:29:58.819 --> 00:29:59.619
Yes.

00:29:59.619 --> 00:30:01.920
Now, first of all, you were in an English congregation.

00:30:01.920 --> 00:30:03.920
But what changed that?

00:30:03.920 --> 00:30:05.619
Our secret overseer, he came through

00:30:05.619 --> 00:30:08.019
and he was telling us about a Hmong group

00:30:08.019 --> 00:30:10.220
that had formed in our sister congregation.

00:30:10.220 --> 00:30:13.019
And he told us we had no reason to be in English.

00:30:13.019 --> 00:30:14.420
And he was right.

00:30:14.420 --> 00:30:17.220
So as a family, we moved over to the Hmong group.

00:30:17.220 --> 00:30:20.920
And in 1999, that group became the very first Hmong congregation.

00:30:20.920 --> 00:30:22.319
So that made us very happy.

00:30:22.319 --> 00:30:26.019
So you were associated with the very first Hmong congregation

00:30:26.019 --> 00:30:27.519
anywhere in the world.

00:30:27.519 --> 00:30:29.220
Amazing.

00:30:29.220 --> 00:30:30.920
Now later, you toured Bethel.

00:30:30.920 --> 00:30:33.019
And that had a profound effect on you.

00:30:33.019 --> 00:30:34.720
Can you tell us about that?

00:30:34.720 --> 00:30:35.720
Well, we came to Bethel

00:30:35.720 --> 00:30:38.119
and a brother in Transition Services.

00:30:38.119 --> 00:30:39.119
He found out we were coming through

00:30:39.119 --> 00:30:41.220
so he wanted to meet with us.

00:30:41.220 --> 00:30:43.220
And he sat us girls down and he told us,

00:30:43.220 --> 00:30:46.019
you have something you can give to Jehovah.

00:30:46.019 --> 00:30:47.420
And that's your language.

00:30:47.420 --> 00:30:50.819
So it really got me thinking about what I could do

00:30:50.819 --> 00:30:52.220
to really support the field.

00:30:52.220 --> 00:30:55.319
So I went home and I really worked on my language

00:30:55.319 --> 00:30:57.220
and worked on supporting the group.

00:30:57.220 --> 00:31:01.319
And in 2007, when Bethel came looking for translators,

00:31:01.319 --> 00:31:04.319
this same brother came out and he interviewed a group of us.

00:31:04.319 --> 00:31:07.119
And shortly after that, me, my mom and another brother

00:31:07.119 --> 00:31:11.119
were invited to serve on the Hmong Transition team

00:31:11.119 --> 00:31:13.220
at the first RTO here in the US branch.

00:31:13.220 --> 00:31:13.720
My goodness.

00:31:13.720 --> 00:31:17.619
So the first Hmong congregation anywhere in the world

00:31:17.619 --> 00:31:21.720
and the first RTO for the US branch.

00:31:21.720 --> 00:31:23.319
Jehovah certainly has blessed you

00:31:23.319 --> 00:31:25.819
with some wonderful privileges.

00:31:25.819 --> 00:31:29.420
Could you just tell us what's it like working at the RTO

00:31:29.420 --> 00:31:30.619
from day to day?

00:31:30.619 --> 00:31:30.920
Sure.

00:31:30.920 --> 00:31:31.819
Would you like to see a video?

00:31:31.819 --> 00:31:37.039
Yes, we would.

00:31:37.039 --> 00:31:41.539
At the Hmong RTO, many hands help in the Transition War.

00:31:41.539 --> 00:31:45.240
When questions come up, we're not left on our own.

00:31:45.240 --> 00:31:47.039
The Transition Services Department

00:31:47.039 --> 00:31:49.039
is always ready to provide support.

00:31:51.839 --> 00:31:56.339
Once everything is approved, it's time to record it.

00:31:56.339 --> 00:31:59.740
Since Hmong wasn't a written language into the 1950s,

00:31:59.740 --> 00:32:03.839
audio publications are very important to the Hmong feel.

00:32:03.839 --> 00:32:07.140
Some support the RTO and other valuable ways too,

00:32:07.140 --> 00:32:11.049
such as cooking and cleaning.

00:32:11.049 --> 00:32:14.150
It's the best feeling to talk to the Hmong people

00:32:14.250 --> 00:32:16.950
and to show them something in their language.

00:32:16.950 --> 00:32:21.250
You can see how it touches their heart.

00:32:21.250 --> 00:32:24.150
As a result, we have many interested ones

00:32:24.150 --> 00:32:28.779
attend our meetings.

00:32:28.779 --> 00:32:31.180
As the Hmong feel continues to grow,

00:32:31.180 --> 00:32:32.680
many are learning our language

00:32:32.680 --> 00:32:37.390
to help support the preaching work.

00:32:37.390 --> 00:32:40.990
When we get together, we have a great time.

00:32:40.990 --> 00:32:47.089
With good food, association, watching the kids play,

00:32:47.089 --> 00:32:49.890
it's obvious to everyone in the community

00:32:49.890 --> 00:32:53.890
that we're not just a congregation, we're a family.

00:32:53.890 --> 00:33:08.599
That was a wonderful video, really.

00:33:08.599 --> 00:33:11.200
Angela, could you just tell us,

00:33:11.200 --> 00:33:15.200
why does the work done at the RTO feel such a great need

00:33:15.200 --> 00:33:16.799
among the Hmong people?

00:33:16.799 --> 00:33:19.099
Well, the Hmong are people without a country.

00:33:19.099 --> 00:33:21.400
And throughout history, they've been pushed from one location

00:33:21.400 --> 00:33:22.400
to another.

00:33:22.400 --> 00:33:25.299
They were pushed out of China in the late 1800s.

00:33:25.299 --> 00:33:27.099
They were pushed out of Laos.

00:33:27.200 --> 00:33:30.000
And from there, they were scattered across the world

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:33.099
to the US, to France, to Australia.

00:33:33.099 --> 00:33:34.799
And to so many of the Hmong brothers,

00:33:34.799 --> 00:33:38.819
they feel like a forgotten people.

00:33:38.819 --> 00:33:43.319
What does this feel like to the first time I've heard of?

00:33:43.319 --> 00:33:48.319
It's the first time she's seen a video, so it's moving.

00:33:48.319 --> 00:33:49.819
So many of the Hmong brothers,

00:33:49.819 --> 00:33:52.119
they feel like a forgotten people.

00:33:52.119 --> 00:33:54.420
But the work at the RTO is a reminder

00:33:54.420 --> 00:33:57.220
that Jehovah hasn't forgotten them.

00:33:57.220 --> 00:33:59.319
In fact, he invites them to become

00:33:59.319 --> 00:34:02.119
part of an international clan of Brotherhood.

00:34:02.119 --> 00:34:04.119
And when they respond to that invitation,

00:34:04.119 --> 00:34:07.420
they find something that they've been looking for all along.

00:34:07.420 --> 00:34:09.820
They finally find a place, a permanent home,

00:34:09.820 --> 00:34:11.219
under God's Kingdom.

00:34:11.219 --> 00:34:13.320
Thank you for those heartfelt comments.

00:34:13.320 --> 00:34:15.619
Really, those are very nice.

00:34:15.619 --> 00:34:19.320
Now, Sister Kang, we have a little surprise for you.

00:34:19.320 --> 00:34:22.920
We really want the audience to know that

00:34:22.920 --> 00:34:25.320
with the work done at the Hmong RTO

00:34:25.420 --> 00:34:27.920
is not just for the United States,

00:34:27.920 --> 00:34:31.219
but the effect reaches clear around the world.

00:34:31.219 --> 00:34:33.920
In fact, we have caught up with the congregation

00:34:33.920 --> 00:34:35.719
in Northern Thailand.

00:34:35.719 --> 00:34:37.420
And I know this is a surprise.

00:34:37.420 --> 00:34:38.719
We did not rehearse this.

00:34:38.719 --> 00:34:40.719
No, it's not.

00:34:40.719 --> 00:34:43.719
But we're going to show you if you'd like.

00:34:43.719 --> 00:34:44.619
Yeah.

00:34:44.619 --> 00:35:17.909
Watch this.

00:35:17.909 --> 00:35:20.210
Well, obviously, they're grateful for the work

00:35:20.210 --> 00:35:23.710
you brothers and sisters do in that RTO.

00:35:23.710 --> 00:35:26.909
Wasn't this a thrilling occasion?

00:35:26.909 --> 00:35:29.710
It was wonderful, enjoyable, to get to know

00:35:29.710 --> 00:35:31.309
these brothers and sisters.

00:35:31.309 --> 00:35:34.309
We wish that Jehovah continued to bless you

00:35:34.309 --> 00:35:36.510
in your faithful service to him

00:35:36.510 --> 00:35:50.699
until the next time we get together on the Inside Story.

00:35:50.699 --> 00:35:52.199
Thank you very much, Brother Stovall,

00:35:52.199 --> 00:35:55.099
for sharing with us the Inside Story.

00:35:55.099 --> 00:35:59.300
We appreciate very much your letting us in on it.

00:35:59.300 --> 00:36:01.199
But I have to admit, this is the first

00:36:01.199 --> 00:36:03.199
really a graduation I've ever been to,

00:36:03.199 --> 00:36:08.969
where I couldn't help but pat my foot back there.

00:36:08.969 --> 00:36:11.969
I'm just so glad I was behind the curtain.
